WEBVTT

00:02.436 --> 00:04.405
"Most likely
to get married."

00:04.472 --> 00:06.474
Billy Burke
and Shannon Philington.

00:06.540 --> 00:08.842
Farmington.
Shannon Farmington.
And Shannon Farmington.

00:08.909 --> 00:10.678
It was a threesome.
[ Sighs ]

00:10.744 --> 00:14.014
"Class clown."
Jesse Pinkercrapper-something.

00:14.082 --> 00:17.285
It's Pinkerfield.
Jesse Pinkercrapperfield.

00:19.120 --> 00:21.089
"Best Wildcat smile."

00:21.155 --> 00:23.624
Penny Lynn Fuqua-Dubois III.

00:25.526 --> 00:28.062
I think Jimmy O'Shea's
a no-show.

00:28.129 --> 00:30.198
No, I think he's a show.

00:30.264 --> 00:31.732
"Most likely to succeed."

00:31.799 --> 00:32.766
Me?
No.

00:32.833 --> 00:34.435
You?
No.

00:34.502 --> 00:36.870
Those guys?
Dad, no.
You're not prepared.

00:36.937 --> 00:40.608
** [ New Wave ]

00:40.674 --> 00:44.145
Ed? Ed Kline?

00:44.212 --> 00:46.480
- Class Romeo.
- Uh--

00:46.547 --> 00:49.083
Jim-- Jimmy--
Right, right.
Jimmy, yeah. Yeah.

00:49.150 --> 00:51.051
Take it easy, huh?

00:51.119 --> 00:52.920
Good to see you.
Take it easy, Jimmy.

00:52.986 --> 00:54.922
- How have you been?
- Okay.

00:54.988 --> 00:58.159
Come on, class Romeo.
Let's go find ourselves
some Wildcat tail.

00:58.226 --> 01:00.261
Okay.
Come on.

01:00.328 --> 01:03.731
Oh, my God!
Shannon Farmington.
Yes.

01:03.797 --> 01:05.599
Remember... me?
Jimmy!

01:05.666 --> 01:09.337
Yeah. Where's--
Where's Billy Burke?

01:09.403 --> 01:12.140
Billy and I don't talk.
Restraining order.

01:12.206 --> 01:14.708
- Shame.
- It was against me.

01:14.775 --> 01:18.312
Oh.
Remember Ed Kline?

01:18.379 --> 01:20.881
Penny Lynn
Fuqua-Dubois III.

01:20.948 --> 01:22.683
Where's your great
Wildcat smile?

01:22.750 --> 01:26.220
- ** [ New Wave ]
- Remember me, Jimmy?

01:26.287 --> 01:28.622
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

01:28.689 --> 01:31.725
** [ Continues ]

01:42.870 --> 01:45.173
* Crack that whip *

01:47.007 --> 01:48.809
* Give the past the slip *

01:48.876 --> 01:51.445
* Step on a crack *

01:52.513 --> 01:54.882
* Break your mama's back *

01:56.917 --> 02:00.053
* When a problem comes along *
* You must whip it *

02:00.120 --> 02:02.590
* Before the cream
sits out too long *
* You must whip it *

02:02.656 --> 02:06.294
* When something's going wrong *
* You must whip it *

02:06.360 --> 02:10.264
* Now, whip it
into shape *

02:10.331 --> 02:13.133
* Shape it up
Get it straight *

02:13.201 --> 02:16.170
* Go forward
Move ahead *

02:16.237 --> 02:19.407
* Try to detect it
It's not too late *

02:19.473 --> 02:22.176
* To whip it
Whip it good *

02:22.243 --> 02:24.245
** [ Ends ]
[ Scattered Applause ]

02:24.312 --> 02:26.314
[ Microphone Feeding Back ]
Uh--

02:26.380 --> 02:30.651
I just-- I just
wanted to say something.

02:37.090 --> 02:40.160
It hasn't been easy
for us Wildcats.

02:40.228 --> 02:42.363
You know?

02:44.965 --> 02:49.603
Some have cried,
some have died.

02:49.670 --> 02:53.407
Some fought the bottle,
some the spike.

02:53.474 --> 02:56.410
Broken promises,
ungrateful children,

02:56.477 --> 02:59.513
a botched
gastric bypass surgery...

02:59.580 --> 03:02.583
and a bad dose of the clap.

03:02.650 --> 03:05.185
[ Murmuring, Gasping ]
Uh, I'm sorry.

03:05.253 --> 03:07.288
I didn't mean
to mention that.

03:07.355 --> 03:10.090
But there are stories
of redemption here.

03:10.157 --> 03:12.226
Oh, yeah.

03:12.293 --> 03:16.597
Stories of hope
and of triumph.

03:16.664 --> 03:20.601
Brad Penske!
Mr. Brad Penske,

03:20.668 --> 03:23.704
he has informed me that
his scrap metal business...

03:23.771 --> 03:25.739
has finally come out
of Chapter 11.

03:25.806 --> 03:29.710
That is good news
in anyone's book.

03:29.777 --> 03:31.745
Joe Graffa.
Joe,

03:31.812 --> 03:35.283
he is an eBay power seller
of hand towels.

03:35.349 --> 03:37.685
[ Cheering ]
How'd he get to be that?

03:37.751 --> 03:42.390
And Mary B. Where--
Mary, Mary, quite contrary.

03:42.456 --> 03:45.826
She has come out of a coma,
as you know.
How long were you in there?

03:45.893 --> 03:47.895
Five years.

03:47.961 --> 03:52.400
Mary B., she's here today.
Give her a round of applause...

03:52.466 --> 03:54.702
for taking
five years off with pay
and coming back.

03:54.768 --> 03:56.670
This is brilliant.

03:59.106 --> 04:04.077
We are America,

04:04.144 --> 04:07.080
Wildcats.

04:07.147 --> 04:12.753
We're its highs and its lows.

04:12.820 --> 04:17.257
Its misfits, its beauty queens,
its brain and its brawn.

04:17.325 --> 04:21.261
Its master, its blaster,
its soul...

04:21.329 --> 04:23.230
and its gluteus maximus!

04:23.297 --> 04:27.100
[ Cheering ]
Its youngsters, its oldsters,
its confined people.

04:27.167 --> 04:29.437
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]

04:32.840 --> 04:34.642
Hey.
Hey.

04:34.708 --> 04:36.744
It's gettin'
hot in here.
Shit.

04:36.810 --> 04:38.712
Pull around back.
I'll be there in five.

04:38.779 --> 04:41.081
Actually,
you better make it now.

04:41.148 --> 04:44.752
Listen to your wild hearts,

04:44.818 --> 04:47.355
you Wildcats,

04:47.421 --> 04:52.526
'cause we are
the class of 1983!

04:52.593 --> 04:54.962
[ Applause ]
Eighty-one!

04:55.028 --> 04:58.399
Eighty-one!

04:58.466 --> 05:00.734
** [ New Wave ]

05:02.903 --> 05:05.873
[ Man ]
* Jessie is a friend *

05:05.939 --> 05:10.277
* Yeah, I know he's been
a good friend of mine *

05:10.344 --> 05:13.313
* Lately something's changed
It ain't hard to define *

05:13.381 --> 05:17.551
* Jessie's got himself a girl
and I want to make her mine *

05:17.618 --> 05:20.854
* And she's watching him
with those eyes *

05:20.921 --> 05:24.458
* And she's lovin' him
with that body
I just know it *

05:24.525 --> 05:27.828
** [ Continues ]
Hey!

05:27.895 --> 05:30.764
That's me.

05:30.831 --> 05:33.834
Jimmy O'Shea.

05:36.036 --> 05:38.539
You were a hit.

06:00.160 --> 06:02.563
[ Man ]
* Calm down *

06:03.531 --> 06:07.000
* And get it straight *

06:07.067 --> 06:09.603
* It's in our eyes *

06:09.670 --> 06:12.606
* It's how we operate *

06:13.707 --> 06:17.244
* A little joy *

06:17.310 --> 06:20.414
* A little sorrow *

06:20.481 --> 06:23.451
* And a little pride *

06:23.517 --> 06:27.187
* So we won't have to borrow *

06:27.254 --> 06:30.023
* Wherever you lead *

06:30.090 --> 06:32.726
* I'll follow *

06:32.793 --> 06:35.463
** [ Continues ]
You think Mom'll
like the gifts?

06:35.529 --> 06:37.364
She's bound to like
some of 'em.

06:37.431 --> 06:40.701
So what was that
last night, Dad?
"Its master and blaster"?

06:40.768 --> 06:43.270
I was on a roll.
I had them. You saw that.

06:43.336 --> 06:46.206
They were just there.
They were eating out of
the palm of my hand.

06:46.273 --> 06:49.009
- You almost got us busted.
- When you're in there,
you just say anything.

06:49.076 --> 06:51.378
I could have said,
"Master, blaster,
cheese and chipmunks."

06:51.445 --> 06:53.313
It doesn't matter.
They were with me.

06:53.380 --> 06:55.616
Cael, slow down.

06:56.984 --> 07:00.020
Do the rules.
Rule one.
Don't screw up.

07:00.087 --> 07:02.122
- Rule two.
- Seriously, don't screw up.

07:02.189 --> 07:04.792
- And rule three.
- Cash out before you pass out.

07:04.858 --> 07:06.894
- Yes.
- [ Siren Wailing ]

07:06.960 --> 07:11.532
Cael! God--
Everything in the TV.
Come on!

07:11.599 --> 07:13.501
[ Di Di ]
Hurry up!
Move it!

07:13.567 --> 07:15.636
[ Cael ]
Shit!

07:19.707 --> 07:21.475
Whose turn is it?
[ Di Di, Sam Together ]
Cael.

07:21.542 --> 07:24.277
Why is it always me?
[ Di Di, Sam ]
'Cause you broke rule one!

07:24.344 --> 07:26.580
Sammy.
We're late for Mom.

07:26.647 --> 07:28.649
I know, I know.
Don't worry.
You're Secret Squirrel.

07:28.716 --> 07:30.851
Everyone, be cool.

07:30.918 --> 07:32.553
[ Bell Ringing ]

07:38.458 --> 07:40.694
[ Man ]
Hey, baby! Hey!

07:40.761 --> 07:42.930
[ Woman ]
Hey! Hey!

07:44.998 --> 07:47.200
[ Chattering ]

07:48.335 --> 07:50.604
[ Woman ]
Baby!

07:50.671 --> 07:53.574
[ Bell Ringing ]

07:53.641 --> 07:56.076
How you doin'?
You look good.

08:05.152 --> 08:08.689
[ Train Crossing Bells
Ringing ]
[ Chuckling ]

08:11.091 --> 08:13.226
Put your hands down.

08:14.828 --> 08:17.130
Put those right there,
little lady.

08:17.197 --> 08:19.733
You know,
I used to think you people
were like leprechauns.

08:19.800 --> 08:21.468
You mean we're short?
No, no.

08:21.535 --> 08:23.503
Green then?

08:23.571 --> 08:25.839
White.
White gypsies.

08:25.906 --> 08:29.209
[ Wayne ]
Isn't that defamation, sir?
You're Travellers.

08:29.276 --> 08:32.613
You know, my buddies up
in New York, they still
don't think you people exist.

08:32.680 --> 08:36.516
Travellers?
I-I don't think we know
any Travellers, Officer.

08:36.584 --> 08:39.386
- Sajick.
- What'd you say?

08:39.452 --> 08:41.288
- What?
- Leerkey sajick.

08:43.490 --> 08:46.760
[ Officer ]
All right, wise guy,
where'd all the gifts come from?

08:46.827 --> 08:48.729
We're going
to a wedding, sir.

08:50.097 --> 08:53.500
"To Jenny...
from Ben and Gail."

08:53.567 --> 08:58.505
Which one are you,
Ben or Gail?

08:58.572 --> 09:00.507
Gail.

09:00.574 --> 09:03.711
Actually,
that's my aunt and uncle
from Kentucky, Officer.

09:03.777 --> 09:08.448
- They can't walk.
- "To Jenny from Kim Wong."

09:08.515 --> 09:10.483
Now whose crippled aunt
might she be?

09:10.550 --> 09:13.320
She's the crippled aunt
of Dim Sum, sir.

09:16.189 --> 09:20.628
- [ Grunting ]
- What the hell's
wrong with him?

09:20.694 --> 09:22.362
Epilepsy.
Takes one in 20.
Ow!

09:22.429 --> 09:25.132
- Got a spoon, sir?
- He-He gets like this
when he's stressed.

09:25.198 --> 09:27.801
You must have
stressed him out, Officer.
Ow! Watch it!

09:27.868 --> 09:29.703
He can't help it.
It's just a reflex.

09:29.770 --> 09:31.972
Ow! Like hell!

09:32.039 --> 09:34.708
- Go get his medicine. Can you
give me your badge number?
- My what?

09:34.775 --> 09:36.877
Badge number.
This is police brutality.
You crossed the line here.

09:36.944 --> 09:39.379
No, no, no.
I never touched that kid.

09:39.446 --> 09:43.416
- You brutalized him
with your words.
- Ow! Ah, damn it!

09:43.483 --> 09:45.819
[ Convulsing ]

09:47.154 --> 09:48.822
Holy shit.

10:12.880 --> 10:15.215
Your people abandoned ya?

10:18.786 --> 10:20.954
You want somethin'
for the road?

10:22.956 --> 10:27.127
You want somethin' or not?
Don't talk to me.

10:36.203 --> 10:38.138
Bye-bye!

11:12.172 --> 11:16.443
- What about the gift?
- Don't worry.
I'm getting it.

11:16.509 --> 11:19.780
Got any gifts?

11:21.081 --> 11:23.784
What kind you lookin' for?

11:23.851 --> 11:25.719
What kind you got?

11:25.786 --> 11:27.888
We got earthenware.

11:32.860 --> 11:35.462
This is nice.

11:35.528 --> 11:37.197
What else you got?

11:37.264 --> 11:39.800
Depends on what
you're tryin' to say.

11:50.410 --> 11:52.312
That I missed her.

12:05.158 --> 12:07.494
What if she's still inside?

12:07.560 --> 12:11.098
She got paroled, honey.
Kinda gotta let you out
if you're on parole.

12:11.164 --> 12:14.968
Aunt Jessie got paroled,
and she's still inside.

12:15.035 --> 12:17.337
Aunt Jessie
broke parole.
Mom!

12:21.274 --> 12:23.276
Hey.

12:23.343 --> 12:26.814
You know your mama's
classier than that.

12:28.148 --> 12:30.350
Mmm.

12:35.989 --> 12:38.959
So what do y'all think
of my hair?

12:39.026 --> 12:41.128
It's... different.

12:45.698 --> 12:48.668
Wow.
You've grown up, girl.

12:48.735 --> 12:51.104
Beautiful.

12:59.079 --> 13:01.849
That's some real
bad hair, Ma.

13:03.150 --> 13:07.287
And so, my lady,
your ship awaits.

13:07.354 --> 13:12.325
Come! The good ship R.V.
We have painted it with dust.

13:12.392 --> 13:16.529
All aboard, including you,
glum-faced child.

13:29.342 --> 13:31.879
- [ Dahlia ]
What happened, Wayne?
- What do you mean, baby?

13:33.413 --> 13:35.849
I'm comin' back
to a heap of trash.

13:35.916 --> 13:38.485
Had a lot on my mind.

13:38.551 --> 13:41.554
- Where are my dishes?
- They were rattling.

13:41.621 --> 13:45.292
It reminded me of you.
Oh, so you sold 'em?

13:45.358 --> 13:47.260
Well, I mean, we didn't
sell everything, though.

13:47.327 --> 13:50.197
- Oh. Open that window.
- We miss a turnoff?

13:50.263 --> 13:53.066
- Hell if I know.
- Open it.

13:55.869 --> 13:58.638
[ Wayne ]
Oh, Mom's home.

13:58.705 --> 14:01.008
Not the candy corn!

14:01.074 --> 14:04.878
Good arm, baby. If you see
a state trooper, hit him.

14:04.945 --> 14:08.781
Why are we livin' in squalor,
Wayne? You could con
the hair off a dog.

14:08.848 --> 14:13.820
Look, I had an existential
crisis, all right?

14:13.887 --> 14:17.157
Is that what you were havin'
when that piece of trash
backed up?

14:17.224 --> 14:22.062
Baby, it has been two years.
Is it my fault she gets all
up in my face with her twins?

14:22.129 --> 14:25.198
You have no idea
how hard this has been.

14:25.265 --> 14:28.101
I was the one in jail
for two years, Wayne.

14:28.168 --> 14:30.470
All you had to face
was how to be free!

14:33.907 --> 14:37.978
Pussy jail.
You played beauty school
and you sat on your ass.

14:38.045 --> 14:40.647
Yeah.
Come back here!

14:40.713 --> 14:42.983
[ Di Di ]
Mom, come--
Come back here!

14:44.384 --> 14:47.620
I said
don't you leave me!
Screw you, Wayne!

14:47.687 --> 14:49.957
Oh! Goddamn it!

14:52.825 --> 14:56.964
[ People Chattering
In Distance ]

15:05.973 --> 15:08.108
Dahlia!

15:10.077 --> 15:12.279
Dahlia!
[ Man ]
Everybody, come here!

15:19.386 --> 15:21.521
** [ Singing, Indistinct ]

15:42.142 --> 15:44.411
[ Dahlia ]
Sharp eyes.
Eyes on the queen.

15:47.680 --> 15:50.583
Where is she?
Here.

15:50.650 --> 15:52.785
I said sharp eyes.

15:52.852 --> 15:56.089
[ Shouting, Grunting ]

15:56.156 --> 15:58.491
[ Wayne ]
The ship is gone!

15:58.558 --> 16:00.660
My lady!
My queen!

16:00.727 --> 16:03.163
Ow!

16:04.164 --> 16:06.699
[ Groans ]
[ Children Cheering ]

16:06.766 --> 16:09.302
Gift for the queen.

16:09.369 --> 16:12.405
We had more.
Yeah, we got 'em off
this bride in Greensboro.

16:12.472 --> 16:16.609
"To Darlin' Jen.
Some days,
you'll find this handy.

16:16.676 --> 16:18.745
John and Meg."

16:18.811 --> 16:20.980
They gave her a ball?

16:21.048 --> 16:23.750
I think you--
you just squeeze it.

16:24.984 --> 16:27.387
Does it talk to you?
[ Barking ]

16:27.454 --> 16:30.957
I think it, like, relieves
your stress or something.

16:31.024 --> 16:34.661
Yeah?
I think so.

16:34.727 --> 16:37.964
Relieves your stress
without a single line of bull.

16:38.031 --> 16:40.567
I found me
a new husband, Wayne!

16:40.633 --> 16:42.535
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

16:42.602 --> 16:45.638
What else we got here?
Oh, my ring.

16:48.175 --> 16:51.010
You all right?
Yeah.

16:51.078 --> 16:54.247
Just freedom jitters.
Damn!

17:02.889 --> 17:05.458
[ Door Opens ]

17:05.525 --> 17:09.229
- There are preacher cookies
at the tent.
- Preacher cookies.

17:09.296 --> 17:12.465
Sweet!
Preacher cookie time
is here again!

17:12.532 --> 17:15.102
There are preacher cookies
at the tent.

17:15.168 --> 17:18.405
Not hungry.

17:21.941 --> 17:24.077
Di Di, I wanna
show you something.

17:24.144 --> 17:26.546
Ever since you were a child,
we just--
Oh!

17:26.613 --> 17:29.482
- Have a cookie!
- That's disgusting!

17:29.549 --> 17:31.418
We don't need another--
[ Continues, Indistinct ]
Oh!

17:31.484 --> 17:33.420
You didn't throw our child
out in the rain!

17:36.589 --> 17:40.793
[ Giggling ]
You don't need
to take your shirt off.

17:43.263 --> 17:45.532
Get your pants off.
Well--

17:45.598 --> 17:48.535
What's taking you so long?
It's the heat.

18:03.350 --> 18:05.552
[ Exhales Sharply ]

18:09.889 --> 18:11.724
Is that it?

18:13.660 --> 18:19.232
Well, what do you expect
after two years,
six weeks, three days,

18:19.299 --> 18:24.437
eight hours, five minutes?

18:26.806 --> 18:29.176
Thirty-two seconds?

18:38.818 --> 18:40.753
[ Sighs ]

18:49.329 --> 18:53.266
Wow. Look at those monkeys
dancing in the rain.

18:53.333 --> 18:56.603
You don't wanna be
a monkey no more, Wayne?

19:03.075 --> 19:05.212
Huh.

19:14.621 --> 19:18.057
Sam still wearing
Di Di's old dresses?

19:18.124 --> 19:20.159
[ Wayne ]
Yeah. Yeah, he likes 'em.

19:20.227 --> 19:22.995
Go figure.

19:23.062 --> 19:26.165
Could be worse.

19:26.233 --> 19:28.835
Yeah.

19:28.901 --> 19:30.937
He could be on crack.

19:32.038 --> 19:34.374
[ Knocking ]

19:34.441 --> 19:38.478
We do not want any more
preacher cookies, thank you!

19:38.545 --> 19:41.814
[ Woman ]
Wayne, I need to talk to you!

19:45.518 --> 19:49.389
Why, Ginny Dannegan.
What a pleasant surprise.

19:49.456 --> 19:53.660
Good news, Wayne.
We're gonna have
ourselves a wedding.

19:53.726 --> 19:57.096
You're gonna marry
your brother?
This is fantastic news.

19:57.163 --> 20:00.833
I love what
you're doing for inbreeding.
No, smart-ass!

20:00.900 --> 20:02.469
In the fall.

20:02.535 --> 20:04.537
Our boy and your girl.

20:04.604 --> 20:08.375
My daughter is a precious gem.
She has a mind of her own.

20:08.441 --> 20:11.244
Your brother here
is a chromosomal retard.

20:11.311 --> 20:13.946
Yeah, well, he likes her.

20:14.013 --> 20:16.316
I don't care if he likes her.
We don't like him.

20:16.383 --> 20:19.252
Wow. Your dad's
lookin' out for you, huh?

20:19.319 --> 20:21.053
[ Man ]
I'll come work for you,
Mr. Malloy.

20:21.120 --> 20:24.123
I can do, like,

20:24.190 --> 20:26.058
real good thievery.

20:26.125 --> 20:29.862
Mmm. 150 years
of suckin' off America.

20:29.929 --> 20:32.299
What you got, Ken,
is a culture of nothing.

20:33.500 --> 20:36.035
What--
What's he mean?

20:36.102 --> 20:38.971
Think you're better
than everybody else,
don't you, Wayne?

20:39.038 --> 20:41.341
Why don't you go and
shit yourself, Ginny Dannegan.

20:41.408 --> 20:43.910
I got powers, asshole!

20:43.976 --> 20:48.315
I could mess you up.

20:48.381 --> 20:53.219
Why don't you talk some sense
into him, huh, Dahling?
You're royalty.

20:53.286 --> 20:57.324
Oh, come on now, Ginny.
I believe my husband told you
to go on and shit yourself.

20:57.390 --> 20:59.726
You can't back out of this!

20:59.792 --> 21:02.629
Okay? It's done.
Your family promised it.

21:02.695 --> 21:06.366
- My family ain't promised
nothin' to nobody.
- Dale said it.

21:06.433 --> 21:10.770
- You got that, Your Highness?
- [ Scoffs ]

21:19.779 --> 21:23.082
Hey, since when does
Dale make the rules?

21:23.149 --> 21:25.918
- Hey, Cousin.
- Hey.

21:25.985 --> 21:27.954
Heard I got promoted?

21:28.020 --> 21:31.991
Oh, yeah? By who?
"By who."
Get over here. Oh!

21:32.058 --> 21:34.694
Feel them ribs.
They feed you
in the big house?

21:34.761 --> 21:36.796
You're skinny
as an alley cat.
Mm-hmm.

21:36.863 --> 21:39.298
I wanna see Earl.
Let me see you first.

21:39.366 --> 21:42.469
I'm gonna go see Earl.
Haven't changed a bit.

21:42.535 --> 21:46.339
Oh, Earl,
it's Dahlia and Wayne.

21:46.406 --> 21:48.508
Dahlia!
[ Bell Ringing ]

21:48.575 --> 21:52.011
She's back from the pen.

21:52.078 --> 21:55.214
Man is not
a moron, Ma.

21:55.281 --> 21:57.950
- How you doin'?
- [ Groans Softly ]

21:59.919 --> 22:05.658
Uh, Daddy asked me
to give these to you
as a-- a welcome home gift.

22:05.725 --> 22:07.494
Oh, gosh.
Thank you, Uncle Earl.

22:07.560 --> 22:09.862
He told you to buy her
some earrings?

22:09.929 --> 22:13.299
Not in so many words, Ma.
Man can't speak, remember?

22:13.366 --> 22:15.301
I took some initiative.

22:15.368 --> 22:18.004
Well, they're beautiful.

22:18.070 --> 22:20.973
Welcome home, Dahl.

22:21.040 --> 22:23.810
You got my cut?

22:29.516 --> 22:33.285
I am the one
with the fingers, Wayne.

22:33.352 --> 22:35.455
[ Bell Ringing ]

22:37.256 --> 22:40.793
- You gonna put it in the safe
or wipe your ass with it?
- Be nice, boys.

22:40.860 --> 22:42.595
Something tells me your daddy
never told you the combination.

22:42.662 --> 22:45.364
He told me how
to open it, Wayne.

22:45.432 --> 22:48.701
[ Bell Ringing ]
What's the combination, Dale?
Has it got a two in it?

22:48.768 --> 22:51.904
Is it one of those numbers
you can count up to?
Outside. Outside!

22:51.971 --> 22:54.707
[ Dahlia ] Hey!
Enough with the damn bell,
Daddy!

22:54.774 --> 22:57.710
Let us get
somethin' straight here.
I am the new boss.

22:57.777 --> 23:01.380
He is the old boss.
That man don't take a piss
without my help.

23:01.448 --> 23:03.416
You look at me
when I am talkin' to you.

23:03.483 --> 23:05.852
What the hell did
you promise Ginny Dannegan?

23:05.918 --> 23:09.288
That marriage is good
for the whole family.

23:09.355 --> 23:12.959
We get in bed
with the Dannegans,
we are in serious koosh.

23:13.025 --> 23:15.762
It is good for all of us.
It is not good for me.

23:15.828 --> 23:19.298
I say she marries him.
I say you marry him.

23:19.365 --> 23:21.734
I had her, Wayne,

23:24.036 --> 23:27.073
all up in the ass!

23:27.139 --> 23:29.241
Who's this?
Ginny Dannegan?

23:29.308 --> 23:30.977
Your wife.
Oh?

23:31.043 --> 23:34.313
Where'd all this
ass-having take place?

23:34.380 --> 23:37.750
- In my room.
- Oh, your mama's room?

23:37.817 --> 23:39.418
[ Spectators Gasping ]
Tell you where
you had her.

23:39.486 --> 23:41.521
In your dreams.

23:41.588 --> 23:44.891
You lost. I won.
Get over it.

23:49.195 --> 23:51.764
Shit!

23:53.199 --> 23:55.902
Get your goddamn
faggot son off of me!

23:55.968 --> 23:58.505
Dad!

24:00.840 --> 24:02.675
Sammy, no.

24:07.179 --> 24:09.549
She marries him.
You got it?

24:09.616 --> 24:12.919
[ Spits ]
She marries him.

24:14.320 --> 24:16.523
[ Groaning ]

24:20.359 --> 24:22.361
I think we won, huh?

24:22.428 --> 24:24.564
Come here.

24:26.232 --> 24:28.701
So where are we gonna go?

24:30.603 --> 24:32.672
Life's a river, kid.

24:32.739 --> 24:34.807
You gotta go
where it takes you.

24:40.079 --> 24:41.981
[ Dahlia ]
Cael?

24:43.850 --> 24:46.352
Cael?

24:46.418 --> 24:48.555
Where's Cael?

24:49.989 --> 24:53.626
- Cael?
- Shh, shh, shh, shh.

24:53.693 --> 24:55.628
Where's my baby?
Where's Cael?

24:55.695 --> 24:58.831
- I'm here, Mom.
- My Cael.

25:17.516 --> 25:20.587
[ Door Creaking Softly ]

26:32.558 --> 26:35.361
Where are we?

26:35.427 --> 26:37.329
Mississippi.

26:40.199 --> 26:42.068
Mississippi?

26:56.883 --> 27:00.687
Well, if it ain't
Wayne Malloy.
[ Chuckles ]

27:04.256 --> 27:08.160
- How are you, Mick?
- I didn't know there was
any Malloys in these parts.

27:08.227 --> 27:09.729
In Alabama, actually.

27:09.796 --> 27:11.698
Oh. So you're rovin'?
Yep.

27:11.764 --> 27:13.632
We're rovin' too.

27:13.700 --> 27:16.202
All the O'Malleys
are down in Florida.

27:16.268 --> 27:19.571
Hey, darling.
When'd you get paroled?

27:19.638 --> 27:21.507
Linda O'Reilly?

27:21.573 --> 27:26.946
It's O'Malley, hon.
Jail'll rip you up
inside, huh?

27:27.013 --> 27:28.480
Whoa!

27:28.547 --> 27:30.917
You've been
rovin' pretty good,
pumpin' that premium.

27:30.983 --> 27:33.052
Yeah, can't complain.
I'll say you can't.

27:33.119 --> 27:35.454
So what you been up to,
crankin' paint?

27:35.521 --> 27:38.791
Well, you know.
[ Linda ]
You wanna come to Tupelo?

27:38.858 --> 27:41.327
We got a good livin' there.
Can use a hand.

27:41.393 --> 27:44.463
That town's got a butt hole
as big as my head.
[ Mick ] Shut up, boy.

27:44.530 --> 27:46.465
Hey, watch yourself.
Come right back.

27:46.532 --> 27:50.502
Get outta here.
I got a little termite thing
goin' on up there.

27:50.569 --> 27:53.139
Best cash I ever made.

27:55.708 --> 27:58.144
Get us some breakfast,
baby.

28:00.379 --> 28:02.715
[ Linda ]
So you don't wanna
come to Tupelo?

28:02.782 --> 28:05.284
We're going somewhere else.

28:14.794 --> 28:17.429
[ Unzips Zipper ]

28:17.496 --> 28:20.132
[ Sighs ]

28:20.199 --> 28:22.935
So how you doin', partner?
Long time no see.

28:23.002 --> 28:25.671
Where you goin'?
What?

28:25.738 --> 28:27.706
Where you goin',
"somewhere else"?

28:27.774 --> 28:29.608
Why don't you mind
your own business, Mick?

28:29.675 --> 28:33.545
That's kinda selfish,
huh, Wayne?
I mean, you're pumpin' premium.

28:33.612 --> 28:38.084
[ Toilet Flushing ]
Now, uh,
I offered you Tupelo.

28:38.150 --> 28:42.521
You got somethin' better,
I want in on it.

28:42.588 --> 28:44.723
You want in on it?
I want in on it.

28:44.791 --> 28:47.526
You want in on it?
I want in on it.

28:47.593 --> 28:49.962
You want in on this?

28:56.836 --> 28:59.839
[ Coughing ]

29:13.452 --> 29:15.955
[ Choking, Coughing ]

29:23.329 --> 29:25.264
Shit, Wayne.

29:25.331 --> 29:30.937
Get one of these glue guns
and pump the termites
right into the wood.

29:31.003 --> 29:34.606
Oh, God.
Oh, Wayne.

29:34.673 --> 29:36.442
Sam.
I gave you a 20, okay?

29:36.508 --> 29:38.510
[ Wayne ]
You gave her a 10, boy.

29:40.279 --> 29:42.481
Come on!

29:42.548 --> 29:44.716
[ Linda ]
Wayne! Wayne!

29:44.783 --> 29:46.685
Go on, go on, go on!
Get in!

29:46.752 --> 29:49.655
Goddamn it!
Cael, don't you shut that door!
[ Wayne ] Get in, Cael!

29:49.721 --> 29:52.424
Cael, no! No!
God, you piece of shit!

29:52.491 --> 29:55.127
Dahlia! Dahlia, wait!
[ Wayne ]
Move!

29:55.194 --> 29:56.829
No! No!

29:56.896 --> 29:59.098
[ Di Di ]
Dad, don't hit her.
Move it!

29:59.165 --> 30:01.467
Wayne, no! You stop!
[ Dahlia ]
What the hell?

30:01.533 --> 30:05.104
Goddamn it!

30:05.171 --> 30:07.039
Where are we goin', Wayne?
What happened to your face?

30:07.106 --> 30:09.108
Where are we goin'?
What did you do, Dad?

30:09.175 --> 30:12.311
Shut up, all of ya!
Look, Dale and I
had a disagreement.

30:12.378 --> 30:13.913
I decided to spend
a few days away.

30:13.980 --> 30:17.116
- They were having
a party for me.
- Yeah, well, the party's over.

30:17.183 --> 30:19.185
- It is my family, Wayne.
- This is your family!

30:19.251 --> 30:21.020
You're bleeding.
Get out of the way.

30:21.087 --> 30:23.089
Mom!
Get out of the way.
You know what?

30:23.155 --> 30:25.457
You gotta take me back.
I'm on parole.

30:25.524 --> 30:27.693
- Take off those earrings!
- No, it's my
goddamn birthstone!

30:27.759 --> 30:30.162
- Oh, shit!
- Take 'em off!

30:32.498 --> 30:34.166
Whoa!

30:40.206 --> 30:42.841
What the hell!
Wayne, goddamn it,
pull over!

30:42.909 --> 30:46.645
- You're crazy!
- Dahlia, make him stop!

30:46.712 --> 30:49.615
- Wayne, you hear me?
God, you piece of shit!
- Son of a bitch!

30:49.681 --> 30:51.517
Pull over now!
Are you crazy?

30:51.583 --> 30:54.686
[ Wayne ]
You're in
the wrong lane, asshole!

30:54.753 --> 30:57.256
[ Linda ]
Dahlia! Dahlia!

30:57.323 --> 30:59.325
- He's crazy, Dad.
- You're crazy!

30:59.391 --> 31:01.894
Pull over, Wayne!
You hear me?

31:01.961 --> 31:03.562
Get down!
He's got a gun!

31:03.629 --> 31:07.199
[ Dahlia ]
Stay down, kids.
Just stay down.

31:07.266 --> 31:10.302
- Pull over!
- Pull over, Wayne!
- You're insane! Shoot me!

31:10.369 --> 31:12.238
[ Wayne ]
Oh, my God!

31:12.304 --> 31:15.207
- Mick! Look out!
- Shit! Stop!

31:15.274 --> 31:17.243
- Oh, my God, Mick!
- [ Horn Honking ]

31:24.716 --> 31:26.352
[ Tires Screech ]

32:19.338 --> 32:23.075
Is she hurt?
No, she's fine.

32:23.142 --> 32:27.279
What about me?
Am I hurt?
Uh, yeah, a bit.

32:45.097 --> 32:48.434
You got coverage?
What?

32:48.500 --> 32:50.636
You got insurance?
[ Beeping ]

32:50.702 --> 32:52.938
Uh--

32:53.005 --> 32:56.242
Just-- Just--
Give me my cell phone.

32:56.308 --> 33:00.246
Just don't move.
You got a big piece of wood...

33:00.312 --> 33:02.348
sticking in your chest.

33:02.414 --> 33:05.051
I'm sorry.

33:05.117 --> 33:07.319
Do you have
something to say?

33:07.386 --> 33:09.721
Go to hell.

33:26.004 --> 33:29.741
She's breathing!
She's breathing!

33:31.277 --> 33:33.745
She's not breathing, Ma.
You're breathing
for both of you.

34:13.585 --> 34:15.687
[ Sobbing ]

34:32.338 --> 34:34.606
Cael, strip the car.

35:19.251 --> 35:21.587
[ Praying, Indistinct ]

35:38.370 --> 35:41.207
Good evening, sir.
Who are you here to see?

35:43.041 --> 35:45.211
Pull around the back.

36:23.148 --> 36:24.950
[ Dahlia ]
All right, can we go now?

36:25.016 --> 36:27.052
[ Wayne ]
Well, it's a long way back
to the woods.

36:27.118 --> 36:29.154
So?

36:29.221 --> 36:32.157
So... I say
we stay the night.

36:32.224 --> 36:34.260
[ Sighs ]

36:36.362 --> 36:38.264
You're sleepin'
out here, huh?

36:38.330 --> 36:43.034
Yeah. You people wanna
wake up with no soul,
that's your problem, not mine.

36:43.101 --> 36:46.838
Just a superstition, Cael.
The only thing you're gonna
wake up with is pneumonia.

36:46.905 --> 36:49.275
[ Sighs ]

36:51.243 --> 36:54.246
What do you think
they were like?

36:54.313 --> 36:57.383
Who?
Them.

37:00.018 --> 37:03.154
They were buffers, Di.

37:03.221 --> 37:05.424
Beginning, middle, end.

37:26.512 --> 37:28.614
[ Dahlia ]
Scared me every night.

37:31.817 --> 37:33.619
What?

37:33.685 --> 37:36.422
Waking up
without a soul.

37:36.488 --> 37:39.725
Every time the guards
turned down the lights--

37:45.331 --> 37:47.999
How long
we gonna stay away?

37:51.537 --> 37:53.739
Should have been me.

37:59.511 --> 38:03.349
[ Dahlia ]
No shit,
it should have been you.

38:05.684 --> 38:08.487
But it wasn't you,
was it, Wayne?

38:11.990 --> 38:13.925
It was me.

38:41.587 --> 38:43.655
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]

38:51.229 --> 38:53.399
[ Ringing Continues ]

38:56.635 --> 38:58.570
[ Woman ]
Mr. Rich?
Huh?

38:58.637 --> 39:01.072
Is this
Mr. Douglas Rich?

39:02.441 --> 39:04.410
Yeah.
Yeah, that's me.

39:06.978 --> 39:08.914
Master bedroom, ma'am?

39:08.980 --> 39:12.350
No, you can leave it
down here.
Right there.

39:14.920 --> 39:17.656
Told you
we should stick around.

39:17.723 --> 39:19.725
[ Man ]
Doug?

39:21.059 --> 39:23.829
Doug!

39:23.895 --> 39:25.731
Hello.
I'm Jim.

39:25.797 --> 39:27.766
This is my wife, Nina.
[ Nina ]
Hi.

39:27.833 --> 39:30.135
Andrea said we should
introduce ourselves.
Right.

39:32.003 --> 39:35.474
Which Andrea
are we talking about?
Your Realtor.

39:35.541 --> 39:37.976
Ah.
[ Jim ]
She sold us ours too.

39:41.146 --> 39:44.883
[ No Audible Dialogue ]
[ Sam ]
They look friendly.

39:44.950 --> 39:48.086
They're always friendly
to your face.

39:48.153 --> 39:49.855
[ Wayne ]
Hey, Delilah.

39:49.921 --> 39:52.558
Come and meet
our new neighbors.
Hi there, sweetheart.

39:52.624 --> 39:55.861
Oh, I bet you miss
your Tampa friends.

39:55.927 --> 39:59.465
My what?
Your friends from Tampa, girl.
Tell 'em about your friends.

40:01.132 --> 40:03.201
I don't have
any friends.

40:03.268 --> 40:06.104
They're dead.

40:06.171 --> 40:10.341
She's brokenhearted.
Left behind a special Tampa guy.

40:10.408 --> 40:12.944
Oh. Well, it was
great to meet you, Doug,

40:13.011 --> 40:15.447
but I gotta get goin'
or I'm gonna be late.

40:15.514 --> 40:18.750
Jim's never late.
He has an 18-hole
addiction.

40:18.817 --> 40:21.386
- Oh.
- She means golf.

40:21.453 --> 40:24.089
- Oh.
- [ Both Laughing ]

40:24.155 --> 40:28.259
Well-- Oh, it looks like
you got the habit yourself.

40:28.326 --> 40:31.830
Yeah, I'm an 18-hole
sinner, Jim.

40:31.897 --> 40:33.799
Love the little suckers
like my children.

40:33.865 --> 40:37.636
Well, why don't you
come along?

40:39.605 --> 40:42.974
Kind of chatty there,
ain't you, Wayne?
Just shootin' the shit, hon.

40:43.041 --> 40:45.443
Yeah, it's a little
too much shit
if you ask me.

40:45.511 --> 40:47.479
Doug's dead,

40:47.546 --> 40:50.649
and judging by the conversation
I just had,
no one knows him here.

40:50.716 --> 40:53.251
What about the Realtor?
She never met the man.

40:53.318 --> 40:55.521
He bought the place
on the Internet.

40:56.588 --> 40:59.057
We will leave tonight.

40:59.124 --> 41:02.561
But right now, Dougie...

41:04.095 --> 41:06.197
is gonna do a little golf.

41:09.835 --> 41:12.437
[ Cael ]
What's he doin' now?

41:12.504 --> 41:14.640
Apparently,
he's gonna play golf.

41:14.706 --> 41:18.176
[ Jim ]
Easy par four.
You can even birdie this hole.

41:18.243 --> 41:21.212
It's about a--
Oh!
Who let the riffraff in?

41:22.581 --> 41:25.350
- I don't know you, do I?
- Oh, I'm with, uh--

41:25.416 --> 41:27.819
You mean old sand trap here?

41:27.886 --> 41:30.656
Doug, meet Hugh Panetta,
biggest asshole
east of the Mississippi.

41:30.722 --> 41:33.692
[ Chuckling ]
You flatter me, Jim.

41:34.826 --> 41:37.095
How's that 30 handicap
comin' along?

41:37.162 --> 41:41.066
So what do you do
when you're not pissin'
on my golf course, Doug?

41:41.132 --> 41:43.869
I'm a lawyer, Hugh.

41:43.935 --> 41:46.605
- Liar, huh?
- A lawyer.

41:46.672 --> 41:48.974
That what I just said?

41:51.409 --> 41:54.713
Where'd you go to liar school?

41:54.780 --> 41:57.616
Georgetown,
class of '88.

41:57.683 --> 42:01.452
Summa cum later, Hugh.

42:01.519 --> 42:03.922
Well, it's a small world.

42:03.989 --> 42:06.324
Bill's a liar,
Raymond's a liar.

42:06.391 --> 42:09.194
I hear liars pull it left.

42:09.260 --> 42:11.830
How do you pull it, Doug?

42:11.897 --> 42:15.266
I'm not your
average liar, Hugh.
Oh!

42:15.333 --> 42:17.603
Here we go, here we go.

42:17.669 --> 42:22.608
- What do you say, boys?
Hundred bucks a hole?
- Hundred bucks sounds great.

42:30.481 --> 42:34.653
- That's a hell of
a golf shot there.
- Thank you, Hugh.

42:34.720 --> 42:38.189
** [ Classical On TV ]

42:40.992 --> 42:43.028
[ Chattering, Laughing On TV ]

42:55.440 --> 42:59.177
[ Man On TV ] I'd like
to introduce the best man,
Mike Pinello, once again.

42:59.244 --> 43:01.446
He and Doug
were roommates in college,

43:01.512 --> 43:05.183
and he has a few words
of his own he'd like to add
to this wonderful ceremony.

43:05.250 --> 43:10.388
"I came in from the wilderness,
a creature void of form.

43:10.455 --> 43:13.759
'Come in,' she said.
'I'll give you shelter
from the storm.'"

43:13.825 --> 43:17.796
Doug, Cherien,

43:17.863 --> 43:21.733
may you give each other shelter
in the rainy storm of life.

43:21.800 --> 43:24.936
[ Applause ]
[ Man ]
Yeah!

43:40.051 --> 43:42.220
[ Sniffling ]

43:44.756 --> 43:47.693
[ Lighter Clicking ]

43:50.796 --> 43:53.331
Come on, baby.
Come on.

43:53.398 --> 43:56.501
That's nice.
That's nice.

43:56.567 --> 43:58.870
That's good.
I won't shoot up no more.

43:58.937 --> 44:01.339
Come on.
Don't do it. Don't do it.

44:01.406 --> 44:03.441
Don't do it.
Don't do it.

44:03.508 --> 44:05.043
Come on.
Jesus, don't.

44:05.110 --> 44:07.245
Don't do it.
Don't do it.

44:07.312 --> 44:09.514
God!

44:09.580 --> 44:12.250
[ Sobbing ]

44:17.488 --> 44:19.390
I want it!

44:24.329 --> 44:26.164
Oh, shit.

44:38.810 --> 44:41.179
Where is it?
Where is it?

44:54.225 --> 44:57.228
No. No!

44:57.295 --> 44:59.297
No!

44:59.364 --> 45:01.466
[ Yells ]

45:01.532 --> 45:03.501
Hey, there!

45:03.568 --> 45:05.871
Damn it!
[ Sobbing ]

45:05.937 --> 45:07.705
Hi, there.
You must be Cherien.

45:07.773 --> 45:10.375
Oh, God.

45:10.441 --> 45:14.212
Oh, my God.
Did you hurt your hand?

45:14.279 --> 45:16.414
Oh, shh, shh, shh,
shh, shh.
No.

45:16.481 --> 45:20.018
Honey.
Oh, look at that.

45:20.085 --> 45:23.621
Oh. You got locked out,
and you hurt your hand.

45:23.688 --> 45:26.124
I got locked out,
and I hurt my hand.

45:26.191 --> 45:28.526
Oh!
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

45:28.593 --> 45:31.930
It's okay. It's okay.

45:31.997 --> 45:34.332
Here's a little trick
I learned.

45:35.466 --> 45:37.468
Where, I don't want to say.

45:38.970 --> 45:42.774
Oh, no, no. No, no.
Please don't go in there.

45:42.841 --> 45:45.210
How bad can it be?

45:48.947 --> 45:53.118
[ Dahlia ]
I was lookin'
for my-my toaster.

46:00.158 --> 46:04.395
You are doin'
one hell of a job, Dana.

46:04.462 --> 46:06.965
Thank you.

46:11.602 --> 46:14.639
Oh.
Oh, thank you.

46:14.705 --> 46:17.408
Um--

46:17.475 --> 46:20.345
Ah, thank you.

46:20.411 --> 46:24.049
What do you say,
double or nothin'
next week?

46:24.115 --> 46:26.051
Sure.

46:27.052 --> 46:29.988
Hell of a shot
on 18, Doug.

46:46.737 --> 46:48.874
Ah.

46:51.542 --> 46:53.979
My name is Dahlia.

46:54.045 --> 46:57.548
Huh.
So not Cherien?

46:58.950 --> 47:01.019
It's my middle name.

47:02.487 --> 47:04.289
Are you scared, Dahlia?

47:05.756 --> 47:08.894
Moving to a new place
can be hard.

47:08.960 --> 47:11.029
Yeah, a little bit.

47:18.169 --> 47:20.471
Here.
This should get you through.

47:24.309 --> 47:30.215
You're gonna like it here
in Edenfalls.

47:30.281 --> 47:32.918
Good roads,
good schools.

47:39.557 --> 47:42.327
Hell, even money
grows on lawn chairs here.

47:50.735 --> 47:52.537
[ Dale ]
Hey, sugarplum.

47:52.603 --> 47:55.206
I didn't know, Dale.
I swear I didn't know.

47:56.574 --> 47:58.376
Didn't know what?

47:58.443 --> 48:00.611
I'll bring the money
back to you.

48:00.678 --> 48:03.881
We got-- We got
a lot of good stuff here.
I'll bring it back to you.

48:03.949 --> 48:05.783
I'm gonna
make it up to you, Dale.

48:05.850 --> 48:10.355
It ain't about
the money, Dahl.
A trust has been broken.

48:10.421 --> 48:12.657
There is a rift.

48:12.723 --> 48:15.060
I mean,
I heard of people
double-crossing each other,

48:15.126 --> 48:18.163
but what kind of monster
steals the family bank?

48:18.229 --> 48:21.499
Think about it.
That is subhuman behavior.

48:21.566 --> 48:24.435
Do you hear
what I'm telling you?
You know, I-I know, Dale.

48:24.502 --> 48:27.338
Do you hear what
I am telling you?

48:27.405 --> 48:29.874
What can I do?

48:29.941 --> 48:33.144
Well, you could start
by leavin' him.

48:33.211 --> 48:36.081
Well, he won't do it again,
on my honor.

48:36.147 --> 48:38.849
It's over, hon. Your name
don't mean much anymore.

48:38.916 --> 48:41.086
- No, my name--
- Is shit!

48:41.152 --> 48:45.090
Every family
from here to Canada
knows what you did.

48:45.156 --> 48:47.959
So why don't you just
tell me where you are.

48:48.026 --> 48:52.964
On my honor, I'll be gentle.
You and the kids
can wait outside.

48:53.031 --> 48:55.466
Please.

48:55.533 --> 48:57.268
I can't do that, Dale.

48:57.335 --> 49:02.507
Then we cut you out
like a cancer.

49:02.573 --> 49:04.309
Would you like that, Dahl?

49:04.375 --> 49:06.411
[ Golf Clubs Clattering ]

49:12.950 --> 49:15.020
[ Phone Closes ]

49:28.099 --> 49:33.171
This life we're living,
we can't do it anymore.

49:34.939 --> 49:37.308
And what life do
you want to live, Wayne?

49:38.643 --> 49:40.578
I don't know.

49:40.645 --> 49:43.681
You should have thought of that
before you took the money maybe.

49:43.748 --> 49:45.383
Maybe.

49:45.450 --> 49:48.286
Let me take it back.
It's over.

49:48.353 --> 49:51.022
Let me take it back to him.
I'll just say you dropped it...

49:51.089 --> 49:54.292
or you got scared
to face him or some shit,
and I'll work on him.

49:54.359 --> 49:57.162
Let me work on him.
I'll find a way.
You know I know how--

49:57.228 --> 50:00.898
Shut up!
Don't you dare tell me
to shut up!

50:00.965 --> 50:02.900
I am barely out of jail!

50:02.967 --> 50:06.537
I've broken my parole,
and I'm livin' in
some dead guy's house!

50:06.604 --> 50:09.374
I am not some asshole.

50:09.440 --> 50:13.010
You understand?
I am not nothing!

50:13.078 --> 50:17.148
I wasn't born
to eat his shit!

50:17.215 --> 50:19.150
I wasn't born
to follow rules!

50:19.217 --> 50:20.885
What were you born for,
Wayne?

50:20.951 --> 50:24.222
An unconsidered life
is not worth living!

50:24.289 --> 50:27.158
Well, I was born
to make my life worth living!

50:27.225 --> 50:30.761
And how are you gonna
do that, Wayne? Huh?

50:30.828 --> 50:35.433
I love you. I chose you
because you're not nothin'.

50:35.500 --> 50:37.868
God, I dreamed of you
every night!

50:37.935 --> 50:40.771
What do you wanna do?

50:40.838 --> 50:43.641
You wanna pretend
to be the dead guy?
Is that what you want?

50:43.708 --> 50:46.511
You wanna wear his suits,
and you want me
to be his dead wife?

50:46.577 --> 50:48.513
Yeah?

50:50.381 --> 50:54.252
You ripped me out
of everything that I know!

50:56.154 --> 50:59.557
What are you givin' in return?

50:59.624 --> 51:02.560
What life
do you want us to live?

51:14.305 --> 51:16.407
We're goin' home.

51:16.474 --> 51:19.076
Home?
She means camp.

51:19.144 --> 51:21.612
- What about Dad?
- Your dad's staying here.

51:21.679 --> 51:23.714
You're staying here?

51:27.352 --> 51:30.588
- Fine. I'm staying here too.
- Don't be stupid.
Go with your mother.

51:30.655 --> 51:33.258
She doesn't give
a shit about me.
I'm staying here.

51:33.324 --> 51:36.194
Run into more trouble,
we'll just find ourselves
some more dead buffers.

51:36.261 --> 51:38.028
- Stop it, Di Di.
- Come on, baby.

51:38.095 --> 51:41.832
No!
I said I'm staying.

51:41.899 --> 51:45.170
[ Scoffs ]
Don't push me.
I know more than you think.

51:54.111 --> 51:56.181
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

52:24.709 --> 52:26.744
[ Sobbing ]

53:24.335 --> 53:29.674
I don't need much,
but I need you.

53:50.828 --> 53:53.331
Now, who buys a house
on the Internet?

53:53.398 --> 53:56.701
A rich man.
The microwave's cool.

53:56.767 --> 53:59.404
Yeah, don't forget
all the dead buffers
in the freezer.

53:59.470 --> 54:01.105
- They're very, very cool.
- Shut up, Cael.

54:01.171 --> 54:03.708
- What about his job?
- What about it?

54:03.774 --> 54:06.377
- Someone's gonna come
lookin' for him.
- Maybe he's a spy.

54:06.444 --> 54:09.414
- Maybe he's an astronaut.
- People don't move
into nothin', Wayne.

54:09.480 --> 54:11.482
People have people.

54:11.549 --> 54:14.251
They got bosses,
friends, enemies.

54:14.319 --> 54:16.854
You gonna tell me
no one's comin' through
them doors tomorrow?

54:19.023 --> 54:21.225
I don't know
who's coming through
those doors tomorrow.

54:21.292 --> 54:23.160
All I know is
who's in here today.

54:23.227 --> 54:26.163
If Dale shows up looking for us,
here's gonna be safer
than the roads.

54:26.230 --> 54:27.998
No, no, not if
we give back the money.

54:28.065 --> 54:30.335
[ Voices Overlapping ]
We're not
giving back the money.

54:33.170 --> 54:35.272
We're not giving back
the money.

54:35.340 --> 54:37.742
Oh, come on, Ma!

54:39.710 --> 54:43.514
- We're investing it.
- In what? Stocks?

54:43.581 --> 54:46.250
Yeah, Cael.
We're gonna buy low
to mid cap annuities.

54:46.317 --> 54:49.520
Okay, what are
we investing in, Dad?

54:51.088 --> 54:53.358
We're investing in us.

54:55.025 --> 54:58.028
Okay, I'm confused.
I don't get it.
What's the angle here?

54:58.095 --> 55:00.731
- How are we bleedin' 'em?
- We're not bleeding anyone.
- Oh, we're not?

55:00.798 --> 55:03.267
Then what are
we doing here, Dad?

55:03.334 --> 55:07.405
The American dream.
[ Cael ]
What?

55:07.472 --> 55:09.540
We're gonna steal it.

55:09.607 --> 55:11.676
What does that mean, Dad?

55:11.742 --> 55:14.845
Means we're gonna live, Cael.

55:14.912 --> 55:16.814
[ Di Di ]
We're gonna what?
Gonna live!

55:16.881 --> 55:18.949
People do it
all the time, honey.

55:19.016 --> 55:22.587
So we what?
We just live?
That's the idea.

55:22.653 --> 55:25.255
- Like buffers?
- Like buffers.

55:25.322 --> 55:28.559
That's the craziest thing
I've ever heard.

55:32.062 --> 55:33.931
** [ Slow Jazz ]

55:42.139 --> 55:44.041
Hey, Doug.

55:44.108 --> 55:46.076
Conner.
Too many lawyers?

55:46.143 --> 55:48.579
Oh, God, no.
What firm you with?

55:48.646 --> 55:51.649
I'm not a lawyer, Doug.
Developer then?

55:51.716 --> 55:54.284
Well, of young minds,
I like to think.

55:54.351 --> 55:57.455
I teach modern poetry
at L.S.U.

55:57.522 --> 56:00.691
Poetry.
Hmm.

56:02.226 --> 56:07.698
"They miss the whisper...

56:07.765 --> 56:11.602
"that runs any day
in your mind:

56:11.669 --> 56:15.773
"'Who are you really,
wanderer?'

56:15.840 --> 56:18.976
"And the answer
you have to give,

56:19.043 --> 56:24.549
"no matter how dark and cold
the world around you is:

56:24.615 --> 56:27.284
'Maybe I'm a king.'"

56:27.351 --> 56:30.921
[ Man ]
* 'Twas in another lifetime
one of toil and blood *

56:30.988 --> 56:35.493
* When blackness was a virtue
and the road
was full of mud *

56:35.560 --> 56:37.261
* I came in from
the wilderness *

56:37.327 --> 56:39.564
* A creature void of form *

56:39.630 --> 56:43.468
* Come in, she said
I'll give you
shelter from the storm *

56:52.342 --> 56:56.380
* And if I pass
this way again
you can rest assured *

56:56.447 --> 56:58.849
* I'll always do
my best for her *

56:58.916 --> 57:01.185
* On that, I give my word *

57:01.251 --> 57:05.422
* In a world of steel-eyed death
and men who are
fighting to be warm *

57:05.490 --> 57:10.528
* Come in, she said
I'll give ya
shelter from the storm *

57:21.138 --> 57:23.073
** [ Fades ]
